  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supro_Promoting Tax Justice Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at contributing to a more democratic, accountable and responsive State through  enhancing the capacity of civil society to advocate for a transparent, efficient, accountable and progressive tax system, preventing the uncontrolled outflow of resources, the widespread tax evasion and corruption, tackle inequality and reinforce pro-poor policies and practices. The ultimate goalis to fight corruption, raise the importance of quasi-voluntary tax collection and increase the tax volume as a sustainable source of development finance. Civil society organisations are strengthened to undertake research, monitoring, watchdog and advocacy actions on fair taxation towards relevant Government bodies and to raise awareness among the general population on tax rights and obligations. The intervention strategy will integrate anti-corruption, accountability and gender and this will be corresponding to the result areas of this project.

Specific Objectives  of the Project:
# To make government to be accountable in ensuring fair and pro-poor taxation policy
# To identify  different issues and gaps in making tax policies more pro-poor
# To develop institutional capacity ofcivil society organizations, students, journalists, government officials etc on tax policy and economic justice
# To engage local civil society with regional (South East Asia) and global civil society movement on tax justice issue

Expected results/outcomes:
# Government institutions will be pro-people and will adopt participatory approach in introducing policies and relevant system
# Gaps  will be identified through peoples# participation for further improvement by the administration
# Mass awareness campaign and community mobilization through information dissemination
# Grass root campaign has been initiated to be linked with national movement through the national alliance
# Campaign related to fair taxation is being initiated to be linked with regional and international movements</narrative>
  </description>
